The paper deals with information rates and channel estimation in wireless communication systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on achieving capacity pre-log in non-coherent MIMO channels suggests that it may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
